cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the segmentation of brain regions of interest from structural magnetic resonance images using a 3D fully convolutional network. The use of multi-atlas guidance and ensemble learning also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of convolutional and deconvolutional layers, which are commonly used in neural networks, indicating that it may belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
